git commands
*****************************
1.git config --global user.name "jagan"

>Configure the user name

2.git config --global user.email "jaganbandi06@gmail.com"

>Configure the user email

3.git config --list

>It shows the all git configuration list currently applied

4.git clone "url"

 example: git clone https://github.com/JaganBandi/git-practice.git


5.git add file-name

>This command used the untracted to tracked (this is called working diectory [identify color:red])
  
 command :git add *

 > This command is added only normal files expect hidden files and directories

6. a.git add file1 file 2 file3
   b.git add -all
   c.git add -A

>Add the mutiple file at a single by using about command

7.git add .

>This command is used the tracked all files at a single time

8.git commit -m "msg"

>This command is used to file move from working directory to staging directory
(identify color : green)

9.git commit -am "msg"

>This command is add and commit only tracked files

10.git push origin main 

>Push the files from local to git hub repository

11.git reset file-name 

>Move the file from stagging to untracked file

12.git reset .

>Move the the multiple files stagging to untracked 

13.git reset --soft HEAD~1

>Undo the last commit but keep changes into staged

14.git reset --mixed HEAD~1

>Undo the last commit and unstage

15.git branch

>list all branches 

16.git branch branch-name

>Create a new branch

